The department of higher education, science and innovation is investigating the possible establishment of a university ombuds office in the university system. Departmental spokesperson Ishmael Mnisi said work would commence this year with the intention to provide Minister of Higher Education, Science and Innovation Dr Blade Nzimande with “informed advice about the need for, the viability, terms of reference, and administrative requirements of such an office”. “Part of the purpose of this investigation would be to engage with the current scope and functions of ombuds across the system, and assess their limitations and strengths,” said Mnisi. To read this story in full, buy a copy of today’s Sunday World or subscribe to the paper’s e-edition by clicking on the link below. https://www.magzter.com/ZA/Fundudzi-Media/Sunday-World/Newspaper/ For more education news from Sunday World, click here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here 